qas.question: What year did the bishop lose power

answers.text: In 1528 the bishop lost secular power over both Neder- and Oversticht – which included the city of Utrecht – to Charles V, Holy Roman Emperor
Charles V combined the Seventeen Provinces (the current Benelux and the northern parts of France) as a personal union

qas.question: What did the loss of power end

answers.text: the prince-bishopric Utrecht, as the secular rule was now the lordship of Utrecht, with the religious power remaining with the bishop

qas.question: What was the bishop of Utrecht raised to

answers.text: In 1559 the bishopric of Utrecht was raised to archbishopric to make it the religious center of the Northern ecclesiastical province in the Seventeen provinces
